Durban - A family of four has been killed in a horror crash in the Durban Central Business District in the early hours of Saturday morning. Rescue Care spokesperson, Garrith Jamieson said the crash happened at the intersection of Dr Yusuf Dadoo (Broad) Street and Anton Lembede (Smith) Street at around 2am. "WeÂ arrived at the scene to find chaos. Two vehicles had collided in a T-bone format in the junction before both vehicles left the roadway and crashed into a fast food outlet on the side of the road. One of the vehicles came to rest on its roof. Three occupants were found entrapped in the one vehicle on its roof, one passenger is believed to have been ejected whilst the vehicle was rolling," he said.  Jamieson said the three occupants, two men and a woman, had sustained multiple injuries and there was nothing more paramedics could do for them and they were declared deceased on the scene. He said a woman, who was allegedly ejected from the vehicle, was in a critical condition. "Advanced Life Support paramedics worked to try and stabilise her however the patient went into cardiac arrest and despite resuscitation efforts was declared deceased on the scene," Jamieson said.  He added that two people in the second vehicle, a father and son, were also injured. "The father was critically injured and was placed on a manual ventilator before being transported to a nearby hospital for the urgent care that he required," Jamieson said. Police are investigating further. Daily News